<title>USA: NCS HealthCare acquires Rescot Systems.</title>
<headline>NCS HealthCare acquires Rescot Systems.</headline>
<dateline>CLEVELAND 1997-01-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>NCS HealthCare Inc on Monday said it acquired Rescot Systems Group Inc, a Philadelphia-based software company providing information systems to institutional pharmacies. Terms were not disclosed.</p>
<p>NCS is a provider of pharmacy and related services to long-term-care institutions.</p>
<p>&quot;Today, NCS's technology is able to link pharmacy sites and customers into a common information system,&quot; Kevin Shaw, NCS president, said in a statement. &quot;The Rescot partnership will enhance NCS's software and more than double its programming resources.&quot;</p>
<p>Rescot's management will remain with the company, NCS said.</p>
<p>((Cleveland Newsdesk, Susan Zimmerman 216-579-0077))</p>
